Continuous integration — what to run, what to gate on.

A reasonable continuous integration pipeline for a python project. Pip install dash e dot bracket dev bracket. Ruff check on source and tests. Ruff format dash dash check on source and tests. My-py on source. Py-test with dash r-a, dash dash cov on source, dash dash cov dash report equals term, dash dash cov dash fail dash under equals eighty.

Gate the merge on all of them. The cost of failing a check at pull-request time is small. The cost of a regression in main is large.

Run py-test with dash r-a to show short summaries of failures and skips at the end. Add dash-x to stop on first failure for local iteration. Use py-test dash x-dist with dash-n auto to parallelize across cores once the suite is large enough to matter.
